Russian forces on Sunday rained missiles on Donbas region of East Ukraine to stabilize control of the region. It was disclosed that a Russian missile purportedly hit a building in eastern Ukraine on Sunday, killing about 15 persons. The incident was revealed by the emergency service of Ukraine.
Local branch of the Ukrainian emergency service on Sunday disclosed on Facebook: “During the rescue operation, 15 bodies were found at the scene and five people were pulled out of the rubble” alive in the town of Chasiv Yar.”
The regional governor of Donetsk, Pavlo Kyrylenko also said in a message on Telegram that “at least 30 others are under the rubble” of the four-storey after it was hit by a Russian Uragan missile.”
Russian forces fighting to take control of the whole Donbas region, have set out for Donetsk after capturing Lugansk.
